From: vyos-ls1046a-build M1 implementation <noreply@vyos-ls1046a-build>
Date: 2026-05-26
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa: Phase 1 — advertise XSK_ZEROCOPY + wire ndo_xsk_wakeup trampoline

Mainline DPAA1 6.18.x exposes XDP_DROP/PASS/TX/REDIRECT and ndo_xdp_xmit
but does NOT advertise NETDEV_XDP_ACT_XSK_ZEROCOPY and does NOT implement
ndo_xsk_wakeup. As a result AF_XDP can only run in copy mode through the
generic XDP layer, and userspace must busy-poll the rings — on the
LS1046A's lightly-cooled 4xA72 cluster the VPP af_xdp worker pegs at
100% even when idle, blocking thermal recovery.

Phase 1 closes the "no wakeup" gap WITHOUT touching the buffer-pool
plumbing (Phase 2) or the ZC datapath (Phase 3):

  1. Advertise NETDEV_XDP_ACT_XSK_ZEROCOPY in net_dev->xdp_features.
     This is what tells the kernel's XSK core "this driver claims a
     zerocopy mode is available"; absence of the bit forces copy mode.

  2. Implement dpaa_xsk_wakeup() as a thin RCU-safe trampoline to
     priv->qmgmt_ops->xsk_wakeup. With no flavor module loaded
     (FLAVOR=default), qmgmt_ops is NULL — the trampoline returns
     -EOPNOTSUPP and userspace falls back to busy-poll exactly as it
     does on mainline. Behaviour change is therefore zero for
     FLAVOR=default; the slot is the seed Phase 2/3 attach into.

  3. Wire .ndo_xsk_wakeup = dpaa_xsk_wakeup in the dpaa_ops netdev_ops
     table.

  4. Add <net/xdp_sock_drv.h> for the XDP_WAKEUP_RX/TX flag definitions
     consumed by the flavor module's xsk_wakeup callback.

The NAPI-side xsk_set_rx_need_wakeup() / TX completion kick described
in the spec is NOT wired here: priv->xsk_pool[] does not yet exist in
struct dpaa_priv (it lands in patch 0071, Phase 2). Wiring it now would
be a no-op (all xsk_pool[] dereferences would be NULL) and would create
dead code on the hot path. The NAPI wiring lands with the rest of the
ZC datapath in patch 0072 (Phase 3).

Acceptance gate (spec §5.2):

  1. VPP af_xdp in copy mode runs WITHOUT 'set vpp settings unix
     poll-sleep-usec 100'.
  2. Idle CPU on VPP main worker drops from ~100% to < 10% (mpstat
     -P ALL 1; thermal_zone0 stays in fan-pid COOL band).
  3. xsk_ring_prod__needs_wakeup(&xsk->tx) returns 1 when the driver
     wants a kick.

With no flavor module loaded the trampoline short-circuits to
-EOPNOTSUPP and behaviour is byte-identical to mainline (M1 baseline
gate).

Spec reference: specs/dpaa1-afxdp-modernization-spec.md sec 5.2.
Depends on: 0068-dpaa-flavor-ops.patch, 0069-dpaa-flavor-hooks.patch.

Signed-off-by: vyos-ls1046a-build <noreply@vyos-ls1046a-build>
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
index b0a325829..baf384ff6 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
@@ -30,6 +30,7 @@
 #include <linux/sort.h>
 #include <linux/bpf.h>
 #include <linux/bpf_trace.h>
+#include <net/xdp_sock_drv.h>
 #include "dpaa_flavor.h"
 #include <soc/fsl/bman.h>
 #include <soc/fsl/qman.h>
@@ -259,7 +260,8 @@ static int dpaa_netdev_init(struct net_device *net_dev,
 
 	net_dev->xdp_features = NETDEV_XDP_ACT_BASIC |
 				NETDEV_XDP_ACT_REDIRECT |
-				NETDEV_XDP_ACT_NDO_XMIT;
+				NETDEV_XDP_ACT_NDO_XMIT |
+				NETDEV_XDP_ACT_XSK_ZEROCOPY;
 
 	if (is_valid_ether_addr(mac_addr)) {
 		memcpy(net_dev->perm_addr, mac_addr, net_dev->addr_len);
@@ -3529,6 +3531,46 @@ static int dpaa_ioctl(struct net_device *net_dev, struct ifreq *rq, int cmd)
 	return phylink_mii_ioctl(priv->mac_dev->phylink, rq, cmd);
 }
 
+/* M1 (Phase 1): ndo_xsk_wakeup trampoline.
+ *
+ * Mainline DPAA1 has no AF_XDP wakeup path. Without it, a userspace XSK
+ * application must busy-poll the rings (VPP af_xdp plugin in copy mode
+ * pegs the worker thread at 100% even when idle, blocking thermal
+ * recovery on the LS1046A's passively/lightly-cooled 4xA72 cluster).
+ *
+ * The trampoline dereferences priv->qmgmt_ops under RCU and dispatches
+ * to the flavor module's wakeup callback. With no flavor module loaded
+ * (FLAVOR=default), qmgmt_ops is NULL and the syscall returns
+ * -EOPNOTSUPP, which userspace treats as "no wakeup support, fall back
+ * to busy-poll" — identical to mainline behaviour.
+ *
+ * Phase 1 only advertises NETDEV_XDP_ACT_XSK_ZEROCOPY and wires the
+ * trampoline. The NAPI-side xsk_set_rx_need_wakeup() / TX completion
+ * kick is harmless without a bound xsk_pool[] (introduced in Phase 2)
+ * and is wired in patch 0072 (Phase 3) when the ZC datapath lands.
+ *
+ * Spec: specs/dpaa1-afxdp-modernization-spec.md sec 5.2.
+ */
+static int dpaa_xsk_wakeup(struct net_device *ndev, u32 queue_id, u32 flags)
+{
+	struct dpaa_priv *priv = netdev_priv(ndev);
+	const struct dpaa_qmgmt_ops *ops;
+	int ret;
+
+	if (unlikely(!netif_running(ndev)))
+		return -ENETDOWN;
+
+	rcu_read_lock();
+	ops = rcu_dereference(priv->qmgmt_ops);
+	if (!ops || !ops->xsk_wakeup) {
+		rcu_read_unlock();
+		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
+	}
+	ret = ops->xsk_wakeup(priv, queue_id, flags);
+	rcu_read_unlock();
+	return ret;
+}
+
 static const struct net_device_ops dpaa_ops = {
 	.ndo_open = dpaa_open,
 	.ndo_start_xmit = dpaa_start_xmit,
@@ -3543,6 +3585,7 @@ static const struct net_device_ops dpaa_ops = {
 	.ndo_change_mtu = dpaa_change_mtu,
 	.ndo_bpf = dpaa_xdp,
 	.ndo_xdp_xmit = dpaa_xdp_xmit,
+	.ndo_xsk_wakeup = dpaa_xsk_wakeup,
 	.ndo_hwtstamp_get = dpaa_hwtstamp_get,
 	.ndo_hwtstamp_set = dpaa_hwtstamp_set,
 };
